methods.name: printJson()
methods.description: Prints the JSON representation of this object. This is for debugging only.

methods.name: addConferenceParameter(conferenceParameter)
methods.description:
Adds aConferenceParameterto thisConferenceData. The maximum number of
parameters perConferenceDatais 300.

methods.name: addEntryPoint(entryPoint)
methods.description:
Adds anEntryPointto thisConferenceData. The maximum number of entry points
perConferenceDatais 300.

methods.name: build()
methods.description: Builds and validates theConferenceData.

methods.name: setConferenceId(conferenceId)
methods.description:
Sets the conference ID of thisConferenceData. The maximum length for this field is 512
characters.

methods.name: setConferenceSolutionId(conferenceSolutionId)
methods.description:
Sets the conference solution ID defined in the addon's manifest. The value must be specified
and populates conference's name and iconUrl values.

methods.name: setError(conferenceError)
methods.description:
Sets theConferenceErrorof thisConferenceData, indicating that the conference
was not successfully created.

methods.name: setNotes(notes)
methods.description:
Sets the additional notes of thisConferenceData, such as instructions from the
administrator or legal notices. Can contain HTML. The maximum length for this field is 2048
characters.

methods.name: newConferenceDataBuilder()
methods.description: Returns a new, emptyConferenceDataBuilder.

methods.name: newConferenceError()
methods.description: Returns a new, emptyConferenceError.

methods.name: newConferenceParameter()
methods.description: Returns a new, emptyConferenceParameter.

methods.name: newEntryPoint()
methods.description: Returns a new, emptyEntryPoint.

methods.name: setAuthenticationUrl(authenticationUrl)
methods.description:
If the error type isAUTHENTICATION, the add-on must
provide a URL calling back into the add-on to allow users to log in. The maximum length for
this field is 1800 characters.

parameters.name: conferenceErrorType
parameters.description: The type of error to set.

methods.name: setConferenceErrorType(conferenceErrorType)
methods.description: Sets the error type of thisConferenceError.

enum_members.name: AUTHENTICATION
enum_members.description: An authentication error during conference data generation.

enum_members.name: CONFERENCE_SOLUTION_FORBIDDEN
enum_members.description:
The user is not allowed to use the selected conference solution (but might be allowed to use
other solutions offered by the add-on).

enum_members.name: PERMANENT
enum_members.description: A permanent error during conference data generation.

enum_members.name: PERMISSION_DENIED
enum_members.description: The user isn't allowed to perform an action in the third-party conferencing system.

enum_members.name: TEMPORARY
enum_members.description: A temporary error during conference data generation.

enum_members.name: UNKNOWN
enum_members.description: An unknown error during conference data generation.

methods.name: setKey(key)
methods.description:
Sets the key of thisConferenceParameter. The maximum length for this field is 50
characters. Required.

methods.name: setValue(value)
methods.description:
Sets the value of thisConferenceParameter. The maximum length for this field is 1024
characters. Required.

methods.name: addFeature(feature)
methods.description: Adds the feature of the entry point, such as being toll or toll-free.

methods.name: setAccessCode(accessCode)
methods.description: An access code for accessing the conference. Maximum length 128 characters. Optional.

parameters.name: entryPointType
parameters.description: The entry point type to set.

methods.name: setEntryPointType(entryPointType)
methods.description: Sets the type of this entry point. Required.

methods.name: setMeetingCode(meetingCode)
methods.description: A meeting code for accessing the conference. Maximum length 128 characters. Optional.

methods.name: setPasscode(passcode)
methods.description: A passcode for accessing the conference. Maximum length 128 characters. Optional.

methods.name: setPassword(password)
methods.description: A password code for accessing the conference. Maximum length 128 characters. Optional.

methods.name: setPin(pin)
methods.description: A PIN code for accessing the conference. Maximum length 128 characters. Optional.

methods.name: setRegionCode(regionCode)
methods.description:
The CLDR/ISO 3166 region code for the country associated with this entry point. Applicable only
to phone entry point types. Optional.

methods.name: setUri(uri)
methods.description: Sets the URI for joining the conference through this entry point. ForPHONEentry points, the prefixtel:is required. ForSIPentry points, the prefixsip:is required. ForVIDEOandMOREentry points, the prefixeshttp:orhttps:are required. Maximum length 1300 characters. Required.

enum_members.name: UNKNOWN_FEATURE
enum_members.description: Do not use. Here only as a default value for compatibility reasons.

enum_members.name: TOLL
enum_members.description:
Applies to PHONE entry point only. A call to a toll number is charged to the calling party. A
number can't be toll and toll-free at the same time.

enum_members.name: TOLL_FREE
enum_members.description:
Applies to PHONE entry point only. For the calling party, a call to a toll-free number is free
of charge. A number can't be toll and toll-free at the same time.

enum_members.name: VIDEO
enum_members.description:
A video entry point for a conference. A conference can have zero or oneVIDEOentry
points.

enum_members.name: PHONE
enum_members.description:
A phone entry point for a conference. A conference can have zero or morePHONEentry
points.

enum_members.name: MORE
enum_members.description:
A link to more information about entry points into a conference. A conference can have zero or
oneMOREentry points. A conference with only aMOREentry point is not valid.

enum_members.name: SIP
enum_members.description: A SIP entry point for a conference. A conference can have zero or oneSIPentry points.
